<TITLE> Ex-minister Tariqul released on bail </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 7(bdnews24.com) Former environment minister Tariqul Islam, also BNP's former vice president, was released on bail Tuesday evening at BSMMU Hospital. Deputy inspector general of prisons Major Shamsul Haider Siddqui told bdnews24.com: "He was released from guard at the hospital around 8.15pm after the bail papers reached us." Tariqul was garnted bail by the High court on Sept 29. Son Amit told bdnews24.com after his father's release: "He is very ill. We are taking him home." Joint forces arrested Tariqul Islam from his residence in Jessore on Feb 5, 2007. He faces five separate graft cases, including illegal wealth and misappropriation of relief materials. bdnews24.
